@page "/account-deletion"

<PageTitle>Account Deletion - Sam Hill Business Services LLC</PageTitle>

<div class="policy-page">
    <h1>WSP Checklist and ServiceLinkConnect Account and Data Deletion</h1>

    ```
    <p>
        Congregation administrators may request permanent deletion directly from the WSP web application
        by going to Congregation Settings and selecting <strong>Permanently Delete Congregation</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Request Deletion</h2>
    <p>
        WSP Checklist and ServiceLinkConnect use account and congregation data managed through the Worship Service Planner (WSP) platform. 
        Congregation administrators may request permanent deletion directly from the WSP web application by going to Congregation Settings and selecting 
        <strong>Permanently Delete Congregation</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>
        Users may also request deletion assistance by emailing
        <a href="mailto:manderson@samhillllc.com">manderson@samhillllc.com</a>
        and including their name, congregation name, and account email address.
    </p>

    <h2>Data That Will Be Deleted</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>User login credentials</li>
        <li>Personal profile information associated with the account</li>
        <li>Contact information associated with the account, where applicable</li>
        <li>Congregation data stored within the WSP platform, including data used by WSP Checklist and ServiceLinkConnect</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data That May Be Retained</h2>
    <p>
        Certain historical records may be retained by the participating congregation for
        administrative, legal, security, accounting, or recordkeeping purposes. Retained
        information is no longer accessible through WSP Checklist or ServiceLinkConnect after deletion.
    </p>

    <h2>Processing Time</h2>
    <p>
        Data deletion requests are typically processed within 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
